Task Title: Implement an Addition Function in Python

Description:

In this task, you are required to implement a Python function named add(), which takes two numerical inputs and returns their sum.

Requirements:

The function should be named add.
The function should take two arguments, both of which are numbers (integers or floating-point numbers).
The function should return the sum of the two numbers.
The function should raise an appropriate error if the inputs are not numbers.

Example:

assert add(1, 2) == 3
assert add(-1, 1) == 0
assert add(1.5, 2.5) == 4.0

Stretch Goals (optional):

Write additional tests for your add function to ensure it behaves as expected in a variety of scenarios.
Extend the add function to accept and correctly handle an arbitrary number of input arguments.

Please write your Python code like this:

def add(..):
...
return ...

Task Title: Implement a Factorial Function in Python
Description:
In this task, you are asked to implement a Python function named factorial(), which computes the factorial of a given non-negative integer.
Requirements:
	•	The function should be named factorial.
	•	The function should take one argument, a non-negative integer n.
	•	The function should return the factorial of n. The factorial of n is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n and it is denoted by n!.
	•	The function should raise a ValueError if the input is a negative integer.
	•	The function should raise a TypeError if the input is not an integer.
Example:

assert factorial(0) == 1
assert factorial(1) == 1
assert factorial(2) == 2
assert factorial(3) == 6
assert factorial(4) == 24

Stretch Goals (optional):
	•	Write additional tests for your factorial function to ensure it behaves as expected in a variety of scenarios.
	•	Implement the function using both recursive and iterative approaches and compare the performance.
Please write your Python code like this:

def factorial(...):
...
return ...
